{
  "text": "To assess the rate of prion accumulation in the lymphoreticular system at early stages of disease we first determined prion titers in spleen tissue and mesenteric lymph nodes after intraperitoneal inoculation of 129 Sv6C57BL/6 mice and Prnp 0/0 mice with 1% (w/v) RML I6200. Prion titers of more than 5 log TCIU/g spleen tissue were determined at stages as early as 3 dpi ( Figure 3A ). In contrast, in Prnp 0/0 mice, prion titers which are due to residual inoculum [CITATION_1] were about a thousand-fold lower at the same incubation time, suggesting an exceptional rate of prion replication in wild-type mice and/or differences in the efficiency of trapping prions. Prion titers in mesenteric lymph nodes were significantly lower as compared to spleen titers in accordance to previous reports [CITATION_2] . At 30 dpi infectious titers in spleens and mesenteric lymph nodes reached 6.6360.07 log TCIU/g tissue and 6.1560.10 log TCIU/g tissue, respectively. Given the somewhat lower sensitivity of SCEPA splenic prion titers are in agreement with previously published bioassay data using the same mouse strain, infectious dose and inoculation route (,7 ic LD50 units/g spleen) [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
